import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.figure(figsize=(10, 6))
    sns.scatterplot(data=data, x='temperature', y='pressure')
    plt.title('What is the relationship between temperature and pressure?', wrap=True)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    sns.histplot(data=data, x='temperature', kde=True, color='blue', label='Temperature')
    plt.axvline(data['temperature'].median(), color='red', linestyle='--', label=f"Median: {data['temperature'].median():.2f}")
    plt.title('What is the distribution of temperature?', wrap=True)
    plt.legend()
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
